03/08/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Montenegro will send three military officers to join the EU ATALANTA naval operation, which combats piracy off the Somali coast, the defence ministry announced on Monday (August 2nd).
The members of the Montenegrin Navy will leave this month on a four-month mission.
Podgorica participates in the ATALANTA mission under an agreement signed with the EU in March.
(Radio Free Europe, RTCG - 02/08/10)
